# Project Guidelines — Backtester App

## Documentation Requirements
- Keep all files in `.agent-memory-backtester/` synchronized with architectural modifications.
- Maintain detailed changelogs inside `Dev_Docs/` for collaborators.
- README.md must be updated if preset configurations or file locations change.

## Architecture
- Enforce strict separation of concerns: calculations in `core/`, Streamlit UI in `ui/`.
- All filters must implement the stateless `FilterGate` protocol.
- Zero cross-contamination between sequential backtest date iterations; call `reset_trackers()` at file transitions.

## Code Style & Patterns
- Follow PEP-8 guidelines with strict type-hinting.
- Resolve all paths relative to REPO_ROOT to prevent environment mismatches.
- Never use bare try-except blocks that swallow errors silently.

## Testing Standards
- All changes must pass tests in `test_backtester_engine.py` using `pytest`.
- Add test coverage for any new filter gate or configuration changes.
